---
description: "Dynamically build Elastic SQL based on use case intent"
globs: 
alwaysApply: false
---
description: "Generate and validate Elasticsearch queries based on API requirements"
inputs:
  api_spec: "{{api_spec}}"      # Reference to api-spec.mdc
  usecase: "{{usecase}}"        # Feature being developed
  index: "{{index}}"            # Target Elasticsearch index

outputs:
  elastic_query: .cursor/resources/{{usecase}}/elastic-query.mdc     # Elasticsearch DSL query for generate-code.mdc
  sql_query: .cursor/resources/{{usecase}}/sql-query.mdc             # SQL query for validation

steps:
  1. Parse API spec and requirements
     - Extract query requirements from api-spec.mdc
     - Identify required fields and aggregations
     - Determine query type and structure

  2. Generate and validate queries
     commands:
       # Ensure usecase folder exists
       - $usecaseFolder = ".cursor/resources/{{usecase}}"
       - if (!(Test-Path $usecaseFolder)) { New-Item -ItemType Directory -Path $usecaseFolder }
       # Generate Elasticsearch DSL query
       - query elastic-dsl \
           --api-spec "{{api_spec}}" \
           --usecase "{{usecase}}" \
           --index "{{index}}" \
           --output $usecaseFolder/elastic-query.mdc

       # Generate SQL query for validation
       - query sql \
           --api-spec "{{api_spec}}" \
           --usecase "{{usecase}}" \
           --index "{{index}}" \
           --output $usecaseFolder/sql-query.mdc

       # Validate both queries produce same results
       - query validate-results \
           --elastic-query $usecaseFolder/elastic-query.mdc \
           --sql-query $usecaseFolder/sql-query.mdc \
           --index "{{index}}"

  3. Prepare for code generation
     - Ensure query is compatible with RepositoryImpl pattern
     - Format query for generate-code.mdc consumption
